Border Neighbors
Using Moonford as the central reference point:

North: Borders the Grand Duchy of Stonehaven (mountainous, dwarven trade partner).
Northeast: Borders the Kingdom of Whitestone (strong cultural and trade ally).
East: Borders the Kingdom of Vaelor (suzerain/overlord kingdom — closest political ties).
Southeast: Borders the Grand Duchy of Brightmoor (agricultural rival/partner).
South: Borders the Kingdom of Redfields (grain trade competition).
Southwest: Borders the Grand Duchy of Riverwatch (river trade ally).
West: Borders the Kingdom of Stormcrown (mountainous, occasional tension over mining rights).
Northwest: Borders the Grand Duchy of Windspire (horse trade and open plains).

Silvervale is not a border duchy with demonic territories — it sits safely in the central region, which is why it enjoys relative peace and prosperity compared to the eastern marches.
Strategic Importance
Silvervale acts as a breadbasket and trade nexus for central Veloria. Its position allows it to supply food and silver to multiple kingdoms while staying shielded from the worst demonic incursions. However, it must constantly balance loyalty to Vaelor while protecting its own autonomy.

